  "title": "BIM Modeller",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong>   \n<br /><strong>Modeling & Drafting:</strong> Develop detailed 3D models\nand 2D documentation (plans, sections, elevations) for Architectural,\nStructural, or MEP disciplines.     \n<br /><strong>Clash Detection & Coordination:</strong> Perform\ninterdisciplinary coordination, identify clashes using Navisworks, and resolve\nconflicts.<br />    \n<strong>Standards Compliance:</strong><br />Ensure models adhere to project BIM Execution Plans (BEP),\nindustry standards, and regulatory requirements   \n<br /><strong>Updates & Maintenance:</strong> Regularly update models\nwith site information and revisions, and compile as-built drawings upon project\ncompletion.\n<br /><strong>Family Creation:</strong> Create and manage BIM\nlibrary objects (families). </p><p><strong>Required Qualifications & Skills:</strong>\n<strong>Software Proficiency:</strong> Strong knowledge of\nAutodesk Revit, Navisworks and AutoCAD.<br />     \n<strong>Technical Knowledge:</strong> Ability to interpret\narchitectural, structural, and M&E engineering drawings.<br />    \n<strong>Education/Experience:</strong> Bachelor Degree in\nEngineering, Architecture, or related fields. Experience in construction or\nbuilding services is usually required.<br />      \n<strong>Soft Skills:</strong> Strong coordination, communication, and teamwork skills.</p>",
